        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 3:03AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 303 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Williams Junction to 6 miles west of
Chenal Valley. Movement was northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hamlet...                         Saltillo...
Hill Creek...                     Pickles Gap...
Little Italy...                   Bigelow...
Natural Steps...                  Palarm...
Mayflower...                      Oak Grove in Perry County...
Morgan...                         Marche...
Thornburg...                      Pleasant Valley in Perry County...
Vilonia...                        Fourche...
Roland in Pulaski County...       Pinnacle Mountain State Park...
Maumelle...                       Wye...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
